Use of the cipher outside the scope of these two grants requires a
separate written agreement with NQP LLC. See https://enqpy.com/use.html
for the four commercial paths.

----------------------------------------------------------------
A. EVALUATION LICENSE (applies to all users)
----------------------------------------------------------------

Permission is hereby granted to any person obtaining a copy of the
Enqpy™ reference implementation in this repository, free of charge,
to:

  - Clone the repository, build, and execute the implementation
  - Run the embedded self-test and benchmark harnesses
  - Analyze the source code for evaluation, review, and academic
    purposes
  - Compare implementation output against the paper and FCD test
    vectors
  - Cite the implementation in academic and professional work with
    appropriate attribution

Permission is not granted under this section to:

  - Redistribute the implementation, whether modified or unmodified,
    other than as permitted by Section B below for Free-Tier Users
  - Sublicense or relicense the implementation under any other terms
  - Remove, alter, or obscure this license text or the copyright
    notice

This Evaluation License does not by itself grant any rights under
the NQP Patents. Patent rights for cipher use are addressed in
Section B below for Free-Tier Users; all other patent rights require
a separate written agreement with NQP LLC.

----------------------------------------------------------------
B. PUBLIC PATENT GRANT FOR FREE-TIER USE
----------------------------------------------------------------

Definitions

"NQP Patents" means U.S. provisional patent applications 64/030,651;
64/030,659; 64/030,684; 64/030,693; 64/030,698; 64/030,706;
international patent application PCT/US26/22552; and any patents
issuing from any of the foregoing, including continuations,
continuations-in-part, divisions, reissues, and foreign counterparts,
to the extent owned or controlled by NQP LLC and necessarily
infringed by the use of the Enqpy™ cipher as implemented in this
repository.

"Affiliated Entity" means, with respect to any entity, any other
entity that controls, is controlled by, or is under common control
with such entity, where "control" means (a) ownership of fifty
percent (50%) or more of the voting equity interests in such entity;
(b) the power to elect a majority of the board of directors or
equivalent governing body; or (c) the power to direct or cause the
direction of the management and policies of such entity through any
other means. For natural persons, an Affiliated Entity includes any
entity in which such person, directly or indirectly, holds a
controlling interest as defined above.

"Full-Time-Equivalent Employees" means the count of full-time-
equivalent employees, calculated as the average over the trailing
twelve (12) months, including all directly employed individuals
(W-2 in the United States or local-jurisdiction equivalent) and
aggregated across all Affiliated Entities. Independent contractors,
consultants, and volunteers are excluded for purposes of this count.

"Annual Gross Revenue" means total revenue from all sources
worldwide, measured over the trailing twelve (12) months ending on
the date of first use of the implementation in the relevant matter,
aggregated across all Affiliated Entities, and converted from any
non-USD currency at the prevailing exchange rate on the measurement
date. For purposes of this calculation, "gross revenue" means total
revenue before any deductions, returns, refunds, or intercompany
eliminations.

"Free-Tier User" means a user that, at the time of use, meets any
of the following criteria:

  (i)   the user is a natural person using the implementation for
        personal, educational, or non-commercial purposes;

  (ii)  the user is an accredited educational institution, or its
        faculty, staff, or students, using the implementation in
        educational or research activities;

  (iii) the user is a non-profit organization, public-interest
        project, or research institution using the implementation
        in furtherance of its mission;

  (iv)  the user is a commercial entity that, at the time of use,
        has fewer than twenty-five (25) Full-Time-Equivalent
        Employees and less than One Million U.S. Dollars
        ($1,000,000 USD) in Annual Gross Revenue.

"Free-Tier Use" means use of the Enqpy™ cipher by a Free-Tier User
in research, education, individual development, academic publication,
public-interest projects, internal evaluation, and deployment in the
Free-Tier User's own systems, products, or services.

Grant

Subject to the terms of this section, NQP LLC hereby grants to each
Free-Tier User a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive,
non-sublicensable, non-transferable license under the NQP Patents
to make, have made, use, offer to sell, sell, import, and otherwise
transfer the Enqpy™ reference implementation solely in connection
with Free-Tier Use. The license persists for so long as the user
maintains Free-Tier User status and complies with the terms of
this document.

This grant does not extend to:

  - Distribution of the implementation outside the scope of
    Free-Tier Use;
  - Use that exceeds Free-Tier User criteria (a user that no
    longer meets the Free-Tier criteria must obtain a Standard
    Commercial License or other appropriate license from NQP LLC
    to continue use);
  - Sublicensing of any patent rights to any third party;
  - Use of the Enqpy™ trademarks beyond the citation rights
    described in Section D.

Termination

This Public Patent Grant terminates automatically and without
notice in either of the following circumstances:

  (a) Loss of Free-Tier User status. If the user no longer meets
      the Free-Tier User criteria, the user must obtain a separate
      license from NQP LLC to continue use, and the patent grant
      under this section ceases to apply.

  (b) Defensive termination. If the user, or any entity that is an
      Affiliated Entity of the user, initiates patent litigation
      (including a cross-claim or counter-claim) against NQP LLC,
      Enqpy™ Foundation Inc., the inventor, any other licensee of
      the NQP Patents, or any contributor to the implementation,
      alleging that the implementation or any related work
      infringes a patent owned or controlled by the user or
      its Affiliated Entity.

Upon termination, the user must cease all use of the implementation
that was authorized under this grant and either remove the
implementation from their systems or obtain a separate license
from NQP LLC.

----------------------------------------------------------------
C. COMMERCIAL USE BEYOND FREE-TIER
----------------------------------------------------------------

Use of the Enqpy™ implementation by users who do not meet the
Free-Tier User criteria, or for uses outside the scope of the
Free-Tier Grant above, requires a separate written agreement with
NQP LLC. Four commercial paths are available:

  - NQP Standard Commercial License — clean annual patent license
    for organizations above the Free-Tier thresholds, scaled by
    organization size and deployment scope.

  - NQP commercial services — architecture review, audit,
    training, custom implementation, advisory engagements.

  - Partner Program — five categories: Enqpy-Certified Product,
    Enqpy Inside Trademark, Custom Implementation, Premier
    Technical, and Hardware Integration.

  - Enqpy™ Foundation conformance certification — for third-party
    implementations seeking the Enqpy™-Certified mark.

See https://enqpy.com/use.html or email RPM@enqpy.com with
[Commercial] in the subject line.

